VTribute to Annamayya
p3
sVnews
p4
VAll India Radio celebrated the 601st birth anniversary of Tallapaka Annamacharya, sponsored by Annamacharya Project, Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams at Ravindra Bharathi recently.On this occasion, AIR presented a national programme of music, with a grand vocal recital by Nedunuri Krishna Murty.  Nedunuri&#8217;s contribution to Annamacharya is noteworthy.The day&#8217;s concert was completely dedicated to the saint composer Annamacharya, as Nedunuri unleashed a torrent of musical melody that left therasikasspellbound. He was accompanied by Malladi Ravi on vocal, Sriram Parusuram on  violin, M.L.N. Raju on  mridangam and E.M. Subramanyam on  ghatam. Nedunuri began withitara chintanaluin his favourite, Bahudariragamin Aditalam. Reethigowla was the next and Nedunuri elaborated theragambrilliantly.Manasija Gurudithadein Jhampetalamwith matchingswaramwas impressive. Hamsanadam was taken for another expansion  but wasn&#8217;t as catchy as Reethigowla. Annamacharya&#8217;sTelisethe mokshamuwas thekrithiwhich was popularised by Nedunuri.Virahapu Rachakein Todi was revealed with a classic touch. The main attraction was the Kharaharapriyaragamand Nedunuri brought all  richsangathisof theragamin his own style.  Nedunuri tuned thekrithiSadanandam Sarveswarawith beautiful music.The violin recital by Srirama, a renowned vocalist came out well.  Raju, a senior and an experienced mridangam artiste enhanced the performance  along with E.M. Subramanyam on the ghatam. Their tani in AditalamforAra aksharam edduppuwas attractive. Nedunuri concluded his recital withMarali marali jaya mangalam.
